{
  "answer": "**Only one poem in *Bang-e-Dara* explicitly addresses the Prophet Muhammad (PBUH):** \"Huzoor Risalat Ma'ab Mein\" (*In the Exalted Prophet's Presence*, Part 3, Chapter 11).[^1]\n\nIn this visionary *naat* (ode of praise), Iqbal imagines journeying to the Prophet's court for solace amid \"this age's tumult,\" where the Prophet directly addresses him as \"O Nightingale of Hijaz's garden-bower\" and Iqbal responds with an offering symbolizing Muslim martyrdom (\"the blood of Tripoli's martyrs\").[^2]\n\nNo other poems directly address the Prophet in second person or depict such personal dialogue. References elsewhere (e.g., invoking his name for revival in \"Dil se jo baat nikalti hai\"[^3] or his ummah in \"Shikwa\"[^4]) are indirect, serving broader themes like Muslim decline or unity.[^5][^6] Searches for terms like \"Prophet,\" \"Muhammad,\" \"Mustafa,\" and \"Risalat\" confirm this.[^7]\n\n**Doctrinal assessment:** With only one such poem, there is no \"cluster\" to evaluate for coherence. It stands alone as an occasional piece: a personal, mystical appeal for guidance, reflecting Iqbal's motif of prophetic intercession amid modernity's chaos, rather than a doctrinal series.\n\n[^1]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, Ch. 11 list entry: \"Huzoor Risalat Ma'ab Mein.\"\n[^2]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, Ch. 11, [translation/](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/11-huzoor-risalat-maab-mein/translation/).\n[^3]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, Ch. 4, [p-9aa6ea](https://falsafa.corpus/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/04-dil-se-jo-baat-nikalti-hai-asar-rakhti-hai/translation/#p-9aa6ea) (\"with Muhammad’s name, light up the sky\").\n[^4]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, Ch. 20, [translation/](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/20-shikwa/translation/).\n[^5]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, Ch. 25 (\"O Mustafavi\"), [translation/](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/25-wataniyat/translation/).\n[^6]: *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, Ch. 2 (\"resting place of the Chosen One\"), [translation/](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/02-bilad-e-islamiya/translation/).\n[^7]: Corpus searches returned no further direct addresses in Parts 1–2 or other Part 3 chapters.",
